Theory: This design implements a Synchronous Finite State Machine (FSM) to detect a specific binary stream (1101). It uses a Mealy Machine model, where the output depends on both the current state and the current input. This allows it to detect the sequence a half-cycle faster than a Moore machine. The design supports overlapping sequences, meaning the last bit of a detected sequence can act as the first bit of the next sequence (e.g., 1101101 triggers two outputs).
Hardware Elements: Uses Look-Up Tables (LUTs) for combinational transition logic and 2 D-Flip-Flops (DFFs) to track the 4 internal states.
